com.adobe.exm.expeval

Annotation Type LocalFunction


  • @Retention
 @Target
public @interface LocalFunction
    Annotation to be placed on static methods which should be made available to the expression manager as local functions.

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      String description
      A verbose description of the function.
      String displayName
      The human-readable name of the function.
      boolean enabled
      Whether the function is enabled.
      String familyId
      Returns the ID of the family the function belongs to.
      String flexClassName
      The fully qualified name of the ActionScript class which contains a method which is the equivalent client-side implementation of the local function.
      String flexMethodName
      The name of the method on the ActionScript class (as specified by the 'flexClassName' attribute value) which contains an equivalent client-side implementation of the local function.

    • Element Detail

      • enabled

        public abstract boolean enabled
        Whether the function is enabled. Functions which are not enabled will be ignored by the expression manager.
        Returns:
        Whether the function is enabled.
        Default:
        true

      • familyId

        public abstract String familyId
        Returns the ID of the family the function belongs to. If this attribute returns an empty String, the expression manager assumes the default family.
        Returns:
        The ID of the family the function belongs to.
        Default:
        ""

      • displayName

        public abstract String displayName
        The human-readable name of the function. If this attribute returns an empty String, the expression manager constructs a default name using the function-prefix and method-name.
        Returns:
        The human-readable name of the function.
        Default:
        ""

      • description

        public abstract String description
        A verbose description of the function. If this attribute returns an empty String, the expression manager constructs a default description using the function-prefix and method-name.
        Returns:
        A verbose description of the function.
        Default:
        ""

      • flexClassName

        public abstract String flexClassName
        The fully qualified name of the ActionScript class which contains a method which is the equivalent client-side implementation of the local function. (used when the expression is evaluated on the client-side).
        Returns:
        The fully qualified name of the equivalent ActionScript class.
        Default:
        ""

      • flexMethodName

        public abstract String flexMethodName
        The name of the method on the ActionScript class (as specified by the 'flexClassName' attribute value) which contains an equivalent client-side implementation of the local function.
        Returns:
        The name of the equivalent ActionScript method.
        Default:
        ""
